---

<BaseLayout 
  title="ComparisonTable Examples - InSpotGO"
  description="Examples of using the ComparisonTable component for different product categories."
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1>ComparisonTable Component Examples</h1>
    
    <p class="lead">
      This page demonstrates various use cases for the ComparisonTable component.
      Use these examples as templates for your own review pages.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-12" />

    <!-- Example 1: Smartphones -->
    <section>
      <h2>Example 1: Smartphone Comparison</h2>
      <p>
        Perfect for tech product reviews with detailed specifications.
        Notice the highlighted row for the Editor's Pick.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable 
        title="Best Budget Smartphones 2026"
        products={smartphones}
        note="Prices may vary by region and retailer. Last updated: February 2026."
      />
    </section>

    <hr class="my-12" />

    <!-- Example 2: Laptops -->
    <section>
      <h2>Example 2: Laptop Comparison</h2>
      <p>
        Comparing laptops across different price tiers and manufacturers.
        Great for "Best Laptops" roundup articles.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable 
        title="Best Laptops for Work & Study 2026"
        products={laptops}
        note="All prices are for base configurations. Students may qualify for educational discounts."
      />
    </section>

    <hr class="my-12" />

    <!-- Example 3: SaaS Tools -->
    <section>
      <h2>Example 3: SaaS Tools Comparison</h2>
      <p>
        Adapted for comparing software and SaaS tools.
        Notice how the columns are repurposed for software-specific features.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable 
        title="Best Project Management Tools 2026"
        products={saasTools}
        note="Prices shown are for monthly billing. Annual plans typically offer 20% discount."
      />
    </section>

    <hr class="my-12" />

    <!-- Usage Notes -->
    <section class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
      <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Smartphone Example:</strong> Standard tech product comparison with all specs</li>
        <li><strong>Laptop Example:</strong> Premium vs mid-range tier distinction</li>
        <li><strong>SaaS Example:</strong> Adapted columns for software features and pricing</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4">
        <strong>Pro tip:</strong> The column headers are fixed, but you can interpret them 
        flexibly based on your product category. For SaaS tools, "Display" becomes "Type", 
        "Processor" becomes "Features", etc.
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr class="my-12" />

    <!-- Code Examples -->
    <section>
      <h2>Code for Smartphone Example</h2>
      <pre><code>{`const smartphones = [
